About this item

  • 6800U High-performance Office Mini PcBeelink mini pc is equipped with AMD Ryzen 7 MAX 6800U CPU (8 cores /16 threads, up to 4.7GHz). It can easily handle spreadsheets (office, work, ppt, etc.), emails, coding applications, web browsing, photo/video editing (PS, PR, AI, etc.), and light games (CSGO, PUBG, DOTA 2, LOL, League of Legends, etc.).
  • Large Capacity and Expansion Options The beelink ser5 comes with 24GB12GB*2LPDDR5 RAM (with 2 available memory slots) and a 500GB M.2 2280 PCle 4.0x4 SSD supporting dual-channel M.2 PCIe 4.0*4 up to 8TB (2*4TB, not included), you can launch and load applications quickly and provide ample storage for files, pictures, videos, games and more.
  • 4k High Definition Triple Displays The latest mini computers integrates AMD Radeon Graphics 12 core 2200 MHz , providing powerful graphics processing power to easily handle the needs of complex design software,4K UHD video editing and playback,or light gaming. The 6800u mini pc Support 4K triple displays (1*HDIM+1*DP+Type-c) to simplify and double your productivity.
  • Multi-interface Mini ComputerAll important connections are available:1*type-C (data & video), 1* HDMI (max 4K 60Hz) port, 2* USB3.2 Gen2 (10Gbps) ports, 2* USB 2.0 ports, 1* DP 1.4 port, 1* 2.5 Gbps LAN port, 1* 3.5mm phone jack (realtek ALC897) port and 1* DC-in Jack port . Our ryzen mini pc is equipped with WiFi6,Bluetooth 5.4 and 2.5G LAN to provide fast, stable wireless signals to connect multiple wireless devices such as keyboards, mice, projectors, printers, monitors, and speakers to meet your more needs for work, entertainment, and gaming.
  • Fast Cooling Mini PCThe beelink ryzen 7 6800u mini pc employs advanced MSC2.0 Cooling System design to prevent overheating and minimize hardware damage,32dB silent operation,to provide you with a quiet office environment.The beelink SER5 MAX 6800u measures 4.96*4.45*1.65 inches, making it easy to carry around for flexible work or hide it on the back of the monitor with the mounting bracket for a more spacious and tidy desktop.
  • Lifetime Technical SupportIf you want to set up automatic startup,please contact us.All of our mini pc obtained FCC,CE ROSH Certifications.We Offer 1 Year Free Warranty,and 7 Days/24 Hours Serving,and lifetime technical issue assistance without worrying about quality,just email to our customer service team.

    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    Learn more how customers reviews work on Amazon

The heat resistance and connectivity also get mixed reviews, with some noting it stays cool while others say it heats up quickly, and while Wi-Fi connectivity is generally good, some customers experience connectivity issues.

    Amazon Customer
    5 out of 5 stars
    Clean, comprehensive, quiet, diminutive and powerful.
    Retired programmer here with 50 years dealing with PCs. This review is not for avid gamers, but targets users that want an excellent home computer. After years of setting up ATX (big case) systems for family, friends and coworkers, I can say I've happily transitioned to mini PC's after recommending Beelinks to my brothers and now purchasing my own. The SER8 had the specs that demonstrate a very capable PC with high speed data processing in every area that counts: memory, cpu, gpu, USB, SSD and monitor support. Along with my purchase, I bought a 4TB M.2 SSD drive for the second M.2 slot in the machine. The 1TB M.2 drive that comes with the PC acts as my boot drive and the 4TB acts as a NVR storage location for my home cameras. Installation of the drive was easy after figuring out that the 4 screws on the bottom are hidden underneath little rubber gromets. The only other additional thing to purchase if you have lot of USB devices (camera, BT Headset, etc) is a USB Hub to plug into the rear USB 3.2 port. The USB 3.2 port on the front I use for my keyboard/mouse dongle. The Wi-Fi connectivity is excellent and set as default so that when you turn the PC on for the first time, it connects automatically to your network after you answer a couple setup questions. Win 11 Pro is pre-installed and on intital boot up, it will ask a few set up questions. I switched the Wi-Fi to Ethernet because I'm old school still not fully trusting Wi-Fi reliability. Truthfully, I think those issues have been fully addressed with Wi-Fi 6e which I have...works awesome either way! After installing about 10 apps including office, I can say installations are seamless and all apps work dependably. The machine is faster than my AMD Ryzen 5 ATX machine and it uses 1/4 the power of my old machine. My old machine weighs 25 lbs compared to the Beelink at 3 lbs. I use dual 50" 4k TV's which act as perfect monitors giving me a ton of real-estate and easy reading. Just 10 years ago, people could only dream of such an incredibly powerful PC in such a small super quiet package. I'm thrilled with this purchase.

      Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
      Size: EQR6-24G+500GB-MAX 6800UVerified Purchase
      I purchased this for my three young boys. I setup a media center and homework station for them off to the side of our living room. I mounted this mini PC on the back of a 40" Vizio TV. This mini PC is quite powerful. I haven't purchased a new PC in about 5 years and was pleasantly surprised at how quick this PC actually is. My last purchase was a Dell i7 of some sort from 2018. This new PC absolutely crushes my last PC on the benchmarks and it is simply snappy fast and quite noticeable even when doing simple tasks.

      I purchased this during Cyber Week and got an excellent deal. I think for the price, there likely isn't anything out there that is remotely comparable. This little PC is a beast.

      I do find the cooling fans to be a bit noisy when the PC is under heavy load, but for our uses, we hardly ever stress the system enough to begin with. The Ryzen 7 graphics are pretty good, and it will run most games on reduced settings. I personally have not tested too many modern games on this unit as of yet, but it does really well with the slightly older games that I might regularly play.

      The case seems quite solid and this PC is really small. Even though it is small, it still has more than enough in and out ports for most users. I have had zero issues with the PC so far, not a single hanging mouse or even a stutter. This is an excellent little machine in my opinion.
